  "prompt": "What are the key factors for thinking about sponsorship assets and rights identification for a large company?",
  "response": "When identifying sponsorship assets and rights for a large company, several key factors should be considered:\n\n1. Strategic Alignment\n- Brand objectives\n- Marketing goals\n- Target audience relevance\n- Corporate values and positioning\n\n2. Audience Reach and Demographics\n- Size of potential audience\n- Demographic match with target market\n- Geographic coverage\n- Engagement potential\n\n3. Visibility and Exposure Opportunities\n- Logo placement\n- Broadcast/media coverage\n- Digital and social media exposure\n- On-site branding opportunities\n\n4. Activation Potential\n- Interactive experiences\n- Customer engagement possibilities\n- Content creation opportunities\n- Employee involvement\n\n5. Measurement and ROI\n- Measurable metrics\n- Brand awareness impact\n- Potential lead generation\n- Quantifiable engagement indicators\n\n6. Legal and Contractual Considerations\n- Exclusivity rights\n- Usage permissions\n- Duration of agreement\n- Intellectual property protections\n\n7. Financial Aspects\n- Cost of sponsorship\n- Value proposition\n- Negotiation flexibility\n- Potential revenue sharing\n\n8. Reputation and Credibility\n- Partner's brand reputation\n- Alignment with corporate image\n- Potential positive/negative associations\n\n9. Innovation and Differentiation\n- Unique partnership opportunities\n- Competitive advantage\n- Breakthrough marketing potential\n\n10. Long-term Relationship Potential\n- Scalability\n- Future collaboration opportunities\n- Mutual growth potential",
